<title>USA: Escalator acquires Coordinated HealthCare.</title>
<headline>Escalator acquires Coordinated HealthCare.</headline>
<dateline>TARPON SPRINGS, Fla 1997-05-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Escalator Inc said Friday it has signed a letter of intent to combine with Coordinated HealthCare Inc, a privately held physician practice management company in Florida.</p>
<p>The value of the deal was not disclosed, but terms call for Escalator to issue common stock in exchange for all the common stock of Coordinated HealthCare, the companies said.</p>
<p>The combined public company will be headquartered in Ft. Lauderdale, Florida and will continue to concentrate its efforts on the Florida healthcare community, the companies said.</p>
